Possibility of filtering out high energy photons to mitigate the heat load resulting from thermalization2 is explored by imposing a maximum reflectance (RUV = 1) for wavelengths comprised between 0.28 μm and an upper limit (λUV). Impact on electrical power output in STC is modeled by assuming that most of the loss comes from a current drop. A correction factor 1−∫0.28μmλUVEQE(λ)qSundλ/∫0.28μmλBGEQE(λ)qSundλ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
